<taxonomicName id="5B964D26FFC2FF84F8739EF8F7C7F9A2" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[2026,2139,1508,1541]" class="Mammalia" family="Herpestidae" genus="Bdeogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="14" pageNumber="319" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="jacksoni">jacksoni</taxonomicName>
), but others believe that there are sufficient skin and skull differences to consider them as two separate species. Monotypic.
</subSubSection>
